description: API design and server-side development best practices for Next.js applications.
alwaysApply: false
---
- Use RESTful conventions for API endpoint design.
- Implement proper HTTP status codes and error responses.
- Use server actions for mutations instead of traditional API routes when possible.
- Implement proper request validation using Zod or similar libraries.
- Use proper content negotiation (Accept headers) for API responses.
- Implement proper API versioning strategy.
- Use proper HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH).
- Implement proper API documentation using OpenAPI/Swagger.
- Use proper request/response serialization and deserialization.
- Implement proper API rate limiting and throttling.
- Use proper API authentication and authorization middleware.
- Implement proper API error handling and logging.
- Use proper API response caching strategies.
- Implement proper API monitoring and analytics.
- Use proper API testing strategies (unit, integration, e2e).
